SIMPLE: smelling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smelling
<hw>Smell"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
smells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The sense by which odors are perceived; the sense of
smell.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Smelling bottle</b></col>, <cd>a small bottle filled with
something suited to stimulate the sense of smell, or to remove
faintness, as spirits of ammonia.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smelling salts</ent>⟦br⟧
